    "body": "Seems like path forward is that we call the unconfigurability of `\"test\"` a bug (and thus not a breaking change)\r\n\r\nGroup consensus (thanks @kevinweaver @eggplantzzz @haltman-at @fainashalts @cds-amal @tenthirtyone @leeftk for the discussion!) is that we should define detection criteria (such as `host`/`port`/`url`/`provider`), where the presence of at least one of these fields would indicate to Truffle that the network is unmanaged.\r\n\r\n(Seems like there's some trickiness with `host`/`port`, if we want to allow these fields as configurable for managed networks in the future, but we won't worry about that for now.)\r\n\r\nThanks @haltman-at for volunteering to take a stab at this!\r\n\r\n",
