    "body": "@Miladinho do you mean you want a long-running ganache instance to be used for all your CI tests? This can be accomplished by:\r\n- starting a ganache instance at the port you'd like\r\n  ```ganache --port <my-port-number>```\r\n- configuring a `development` network\r\n  ```javascript\r\n    networks: {\r\n      development: {\r\n       host: \"127.0.0.1\",     \r\n       port: <my-port-number>,            \r\n       network_id: \"*\",    \r\n      },\r\n    }\r\n    // etc...\r\n  ```\r\n\r\nNOTE: You could also define a `test` network, however Truffle will use `development` if it also exists.\r\n",
